      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "It's always a good idea to find a viewpoint from above when exploring a new city. Our friend highly recommended the view from "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "the thirteenth century tower at the"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "University Church of St. Mary's"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and we are so glad she did! The journey up the tower is neat itself - there is a little exhibit before you reach the highest point. The winding staircase and the top of the tower are tiny, leaving very little room to move around other people, but I kind of liked how that added to the unique-ness of the experience.  Regarding the view, I'll let the pictures speak for themselves...."
          },
          {
