      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "It really started to pour after our college tours, so we ran to find the coffee shop our friend recommended, the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "The Missing Bean"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".  It had great coffee, and a fun, student vibe."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "As library and bookstore lovers, we knew we had to do one of the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "guided tours of Oxford's Bodleian Library"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". They offer a variety of options, including the mini, standard, and extended tours, and they encourage you to book your tickets ahead of time to secure a spot on your tour of choice. The mini tour (advertised as half an hour) was the only one that fit our schedule, but it ended up being longer (about 45 minutes) and very informative. Unfortunately, pictures were not allowed in Duke Humfrey's Library, a gorgeous, centuries-old reading room. However, you can see it in three of the Harry Potter films because it was used as the Hogwarts library (Sorcerer's Stone, Chamber of Secrets, and Goblet of Fire). This part of the library houses many, many important works that the students are actually allowed to reference under the supervision of a librarian."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
